author: adrianc
msg: The original Ajax work was a great start, but there were limitations. These changes open things up a bit: 1) Ajax rendering falls back to plain HTML when the user has JavaScript disabled. 2) You can have more than one area updated during an event.
IE7 updates only <div> elements, so be aware of that when using the Ajax feature.
See the Example component for a demonstration.
